0.9.0-rc1.name: react
0.9.0-rc1.description: An npm package to get you immediate access to [React](http://facebook.github.io/react/), without also requiring the JSX transformer. This is especially useful for cases where you want to [`browserify`](https://github.com/substack/node-browserify) your module using `React`.

0.8.0.name: react
0.8.0.description: An npm package to get you immediate access to [React](http://facebook.github.io/react/), without also requiring the JSX transformer. This is especially useful for cases where you want to [`browserify`](https://github.com/substack/node-browserify) your module using `React`.

0.7.1.name: react
0.7.1.description: React is a javascript module implementing a lightweight rules engine to make it easier to work with asynchronous code, by reducing boilerplate code and improving error and exception handling while allowing variable and task dependencies when defining flow.
